Basic curl commands for onhandl AI Provider API

## Test Connection


# Test OpenAI
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/ai/test-connection \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"provider": "openai"}'

# Test Anthropic
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/ai/test-connection \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"provider": "anthropic"}'

# Test Gemini
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/ai/test-connection \
  -H "Content-Type": "application/json" \
  -d '{"provider": "gemini"}'

# Test Ollama
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/ai/test-connection \
  -H "Content-Type": "application/json" \
  -d '{"provider": "ollama"}'


## Completion Endpoint

```bash
# Basic completion (uses system defaults)
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/ai/complete \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello"}]
  }'

# With specific provider
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/ai/complete \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "provider": "anthropic",
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello"}]
  }'

# With system prompt
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/ai/complete \
  -H "Content-Type": application/json" \
  -d '{
    "messages": [
      {"role": "system", "content": "You are a pirate"},
      {"role": "user", "content": "Say hello"}
    ]
  }'

# Multi-turn conversation
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/ai/complete \
  -H "Content-Type": application/json" \
  -d '{
    "messages": [
      {"role": "user", "content": "My name is John"},
      {"role": "assistant", "content": "Nice to meet you John!"},
      {"role": "user", "content": "What is my name?"}
    ]
  }'

# With temperature and max tokens
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/ai/complete \
  -H "Content-Type": application/json" \
  -d '{
    "provider": "anthropic",
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Write a poem"}],
    "temperature": 0.9,
    "maxTokens": 200
  }'

# Override API key in request body
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/ai/complete \
  -H "Content-Type": application/json" \
  -d '{
    "provider": "openai",
    "apiKey": "your-custom-key",
    "baseUrl": "https://your-endpoint.com",
    "model": "gpt-4",
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello"}]
  }'

# Use header for API key
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/ai/complete \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "X-AI-API-Key: your-custom-key" \
  -d '{
    "provider": "openai",
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello"}]
  }'

# With agent context
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/ai/complete \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "provider": "anthropic",
    "agentId": "your-agent-id",
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "What can you do?"}]
  }'


## Streaming Endpoint


# Basic streaming
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/ai/stream \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Count to 5"}]
  }'

# Stream with specific provider
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/ai/stream \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "provider": "anthropic",
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Tell me a story"}]
  }'

# Stream with system prompt
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/ai/stream \
  -H "Content-Type": application/json" \
  -d '{
    "messages": [
      {"role": "system", "content": "You are a helpful assistant"},
      {"role": "user", "content": "Explain quantum computing"}
    ]
  }'

# Stream with custom settings
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/ai/stream \
  -H "Content-Type": application/json" \
  -d '{
    "provider": "openai",
    "model": "gpt-5.4",
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Write a haiku"}],
    "temperature": 0.8,
    "maxTokens": 100
  }'

# Stream with header API key
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/ai/stream \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "X-AI-API-Key: your-custom-key" \
  -d '{
    "provider": "anthropic",
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Say hi"}]
    }'
  

